          <details>
            <summary>How do I calculate hours worked?</summary>
            <p>Select "Time difference", enter your start time (e.g. 09:00) and end time (e.g. 17:30). The calculator will show you worked 8 hours 30 minutes.</p>
          </details>
          <details>
            <summary>Does it work for night shifts that cross midnight?</summary>
            <p>Yes. If the end time is earlier than the start time, the calculator assumes the shift crossed midnight and calculates correctly.</p>
          </details>
          <details>
            <summary>Can I add more than two durations?</summary>
            <p>Add the first two, then use the result as the first duration with the next one.</p>
